    {
      "sender": "jupyter-ai-personas::jupyter_ai_quickagent::QuickAgentPersona",
      "id": "feae9b0a-ff25-485d-b68b-bcc3cc6be862",
      "body": "I'll analyze the folder following the researcher skill workflow. Let me start by inventorying the files.Excellent dataset \u2014 50,000 students, 16 columns, mixing GenAI usage, study habits, and academic outcomes. Let me report the inventory and propose research questions.\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1 \u2014 Inventory\n\n**Folder:** `~/Downloads/student_ai/` (1 file)\n\n**`ai_student_impact_dataset.csv`** \u2014 50,000 rows \u00d7 16 columns. No missing values. Variables include:\n- **Demographics:** Student_ID, Major_Category (5 levels), Year_of_Study (5 levels)\n- **Academic baseline/outcome:** Pre_Semester_GPA, Post_Semester_GPA, Skill_Retention_Score\n- **GenAI usage:** Weekly_GenAI_Hours, Primary_Use_Case (5 levels), Prompt_Engineering_Skill, Tool_Diversity, Paid_Subscription, Perceived_AI_Dependency\n- **Context/wellbeing:** Traditional_Study_Hours, Institutional_Policy, Anxiety_Level_During_Exams, Burnout_Risk_Level\n\n**Initial signals from correlations:**\n- `Pre_GPA \u2192 Post_GPA` r = 0.927 (very strong baseline carryover)\n- `Weekly_GenAI_Hours \u2194 Perceived_AI_Dependency` r = 0.665\n- `Weekly_GenAI_Hours \u2194 Anxiety` r = 0.269\n- `Weekly_GenAI_Hours \u2194 Skill_Retention` r = \u22120.118\n- `Weekly_GenAI_Hours \u2194 Traditional_Study_Hours` r = \u22120.157\n- `Tool_Diversity \u2194 Skill_Retention` r = 0.197\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2 \u2014 Proposed Research Questions\n\n**RQ1 (primary):** *Does heavier weekly GenAI use harm GPA growth (Post \u2212 Pre) and skill retention, after controlling for major, year, prompt-engineering skill, and traditional study hours?*\n\n**RQ2:** *Does institutional policy (Strict_Ban / Allowed_With_Citation / Actively_Encouraged) moderate the relationship between GenAI usage and academic outcomes?*\n\n**RQ3:** *Which factors most predict high burnout risk and exam anxiety \u2014 is it raw GenAI hours, perceived dependency, or low traditional study time?*\n\n---\n\nShall I proceed with **all three** (they share the data pipeline and combine into a coherent paper), or would you like to focus on one? If no preference, I'll proceed with all three.",
      "type": "msg",
      "raw_time": false,
      "time": 1779670170.0909472,
      "mentions": []
    },
